[New Japanese name: Fuka-mizo-karuishi-kobushi] (
Figs. 1–4
)

Ambulatory legs (Figs. 2, 3F, 
4
) short; meri stout, densely covered with flattened granules, with row of large tubercles on proximal half to four-fifths of extensor margin, on upper, lower angle of flexor surface; carpi, propodi, dactyli densely covered with low, sometimes indistinct granules; granules on surface of dactyli, microscopic, subacute.
